SR NO. 176 ENROLLED
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby urge and request the office of alcohol and tobacco control and the Board of
Regents to conduct a joint study on the feasibility of allowing student identification cards
issued by Louisiana postsecondary institutions to be used for digital identification
verification, including but not limited to age verification for alcohol and tobacco purchases.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study shall include, at minimum:
(1) An evaluation of technological requirements and security standards necessary for
digital verification.
(2) An assessment of privacy and data-protection implications for students and
institutions, as well as savings for both.
(3) A review of potential costs, funding needs, and implementation timelines.
(4) Consultation with Louisiana higher education systems, campus security officials,
relevant technology experts, and best practices from other states.
(5) Identification of any statutory or regulatory changes required to authorize such
use.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the office of alcohol and tobacco control and the
Board of Regents shall submit a written report of findings and recommendations to the
Senate Committee on Judiciary B and the Senate Committee on Education no later than
February 1, 2027.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
commissioner of the office of alcohol and tobacco control and the commissioner of higher
education.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
